Using a Tree Model

-We can do this automagically

-There are many models based upon this concept

-Let's use a simple decision tree model

Creating Training and Testing Sets

set.seed(4)

train.integers <- createDataPartition(y = hr.data$left, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)

training <- hr.data[train.integers, ]
testing <- hr.data[-train.integers, ]

Growing and Admiring a Tree

tree.fit <- train(left ~ ., data = training,
                  method = "rpart")

plot(tree.fit$finalModel)
text(tree.fit$finalModel)

Evaluating our Tree

tree.pred <- predict(tree.fit, newdata = testing)
confusionMatrix(data = tree.pred, testing$left)
